Spring Tennoushou

00:10:19.320 --> 00:10:20.140
Undefeated!

00:10:20.140 --> 00:10:20.940
Reigning!

00:10:20.940 --> 00:10:21.610
Undefeated!

00:10:21.610 --> 00:10:22.280
Reigning!

00:10:22.280 --> 00:10:26.550
The Spring Tennoushou is 3,200 meters, 
making it the longest in the G1.

00:10:26.550 --> 00:10:29.330
The ability to perform well as a 
stayer is going to be crucial.

00:10:29.330 --> 00:10:30.170
What brought all this on?

00:10:30.170 --> 00:10:31.470
The previous champ, McQueen,

00:10:31.470 --> 00:10:34.210
is coming into this after running 
the 3,000 meter Hanshin Daishoten...

00:10:34.210 --> 00:10:37.300
But Teio just sprinted through 
the 2,000 meter Osaka Hai.

00:10:37.300 --> 00:10:39.060
Teio comes out on top in popularity,

00:10:39.060 --> 00:10:42.070
but does she really have the 
long-distance legs to rival McQueen?

00:10:42.070 --> 00:10:46.060
True enough, and Teio's longest race was 
the Derby, which is only 2,400 meters.

00:10:46.060 --> 00:10:48.110
Teio-san's not gonna lose!

00:10:48.110 --> 00:10:49.230
S-Sorry!

00:10:50.710 --> 00:10:52.730
Let's make sure to remember every moment.

00:10:54.130 --> 00:10:55.730
Yeah, you're right.

00:10:55.730 --> 00:10:58.330
This is a serious race between two 
of the most dazzling horse girls.

00:10:58.330 --> 00:11:00.860
We'd better make sure to take it all in.

00:11:01.530 --> 00:11:03.220
Why are you in your racing gear?

00:11:03.990 --> 00:11:07.520
So that I'll be able to hit the field if 
there are any horse girls who don't show up!

00:11:31.650 --> 00:11:35.860
If you do lose, please try not to cry.

00:11:36.750 --> 00:11:40.120
Just be ready to be one of my backup 
dancers at the Winning Concert.

00:11:49.310 --> 00:11:50.450
Go on ahead.

00:11:50.450 --> 00:11:51.760
By all means, you first.

00:11:51.760 --> 00:11:52.680
Oh, I couldn't! You go.

00:11:52.680 --> 00:11:54.190
No, I really must insist.

00:11:55.190 --> 00:11:56.950
Rock-paper-scissors—

00:11:59.590 --> 00:12:00.900
There she is!

00:12:00.900 --> 00:12:05.220
Aiming for the first ever consecutive 
Tennoushou win, it's Mejiro McQueen!

00:12:05.220 --> 00:12:08.720
Her fans have packed the track, 
and are greeting her with cheers!

00:12:08.720 --> 00:12:11.220
Her new racing gear is quite lovely.

00:12:11.870 --> 00:12:12.930
So cool!

00:12:12.930 --> 00:12:16.150
McQueen-san... you're so dreamy!

00:12:16.150 --> 00:12:18.470
Ready, and...

00:12:18.470 --> 00:12:20.650
You can do it, McQueen!

00:12:19.640 --> 00:12:20.650
...san!

00:12:23.610 --> 00:12:26.040
And now, the star has arrived.

00:12:26.620 --> 00:12:29.800
Seven races, and seven wins: Tokai Teio!

00:12:30.270 --> 00:12:31.770
She certainly looks ready.

00:12:32.120 --> 00:12:34.120
Teio!

00:12:36.120 --> 00:12:37.790
Her aura is amazing!

00:12:37.790 --> 00:12:40.260
Please win, McQueen-san!

00:12:40.260 --> 00:12:42.630
You've got this, Teio-san!

00:12:42.630 --> 00:12:43.910
Ready, and...

00:12:43.910 --> 00:12:45.760
You can do it, Teio!

00:12:44.910 --> 00:12:45.760
...san!

00:12:47.760 --> 00:12:49.890
I don't know if I've ever 
seen a more excited crowd.

00:12:49.890 --> 00:12:51.180
You're right.

00:12:51.180 --> 00:12:53.360
They <i>were</i> excited when 
you were running, Rudolf-chan.

00:12:53.360 --> 00:12:56.650
No, today's response is 
much bigger than mine was.

00:12:56.940 --> 00:13:00.300
I wish I had a rival to
race against, the way they do.

00:13:09.870 --> 00:13:11.840
Who do I root for?

00:13:11.840 --> 00:13:13.200
Both of them, of course!

00:13:13.580 --> 00:13:16.030
I'm gonna outrun everybody today, ultimately!

00:13:23.590 --> 00:13:25.590
McQueen's

00:13:23.590 --> 00:13:25.600
I-Is this...

00:13:25.600 --> 00:13:26.780
McQueen!

00:13:28.340 --> 00:13:29.960
We have an announcement.

00:13:29.960 --> 00:13:32.590
Due to one of Mejiro McQueen's 
horseshoes coming off,

00:13:32.590 --> 00:13:36.600
and the need to reapply it, there will 
be a delay in the start of the race.

00:13:37.020 --> 00:13:38.110
Oh, no...

00:13:38.590 --> 00:13:40.460
Huh? McQueen-san...

00:13:40.460 --> 00:13:41.570
Is she gonna be okay?

00:13:41.570 --> 00:13:43.430
This has happened before, hasn't it?

00:13:43.430 --> 00:13:44.550
Yeah, I remember.

00:13:44.550 --> 00:13:48.020
It happened to the most popular horse girl
at the time, but she ended up losing after.

00:13:48.020 --> 00:13:49.700
Oh man, I've got a bad feeling about this.

00:13:49.700 --> 00:13:51.510
No bad feelings allowed!

00:13:51.510 --> 00:13:52.700
S-Sorry!

00:13:54.700 --> 00:13:58.280
Don't lose your focus, McQueen!

00:14:02.900 --> 00:14:05.710
Teio's staying calm through the wait, huh?

00:14:05.710 --> 00:14:09.100
This is like the duel between Miyamoto Musashi
 and Sasaki Kojiro at Ganryuu Island.

00:14:09.100 --> 00:14:11.630
Which one is Miyamoto Musashi, in this case?

00:14:12.850 --> 00:14:15.220
Is it Turbo's time to shine?

00:14:17.230 --> 00:14:21.730
It looks like Mejiro McQueen has 
finished with her horseshoe.

00:14:21.730 --> 00:14:25.980
Despite the incident, she doesn't 
seem to have lost her composure.

00:14:26.940 --> 00:14:29.590
The fanfare signaling the start 
of the match of the millennium

00:14:29.590 --> 00:14:31.710
has begun to play throughout 
the Kyoto Racecourse.

00:14:31.710 --> 00:14:33.580
Just who will win?

00:14:33.580 --> 00:14:39.280
Each horse girl enters her gate, 
looking ready to struggle for supremacy.

00:14:39.280 --> 00:14:43.630
And last up is Tokai Teio, 
entering #14 on the outside.

00:14:46.110 --> 00:14:47.740
Teio-san!

00:14:46.800 --> 00:14:48.130
McQueen-san!

00:14:50.380 --> 00:14:55.260
Now, who will leave the Spring 
Tennoushou victorious? The 7-0 Tokai Teio?

00:14:55.260 --> 00:14:58.770
Or the strongest stayer, Mejiro McQueen?

00:14:58.770 --> 00:15:01.690
These 14 horse girls are putting 
their pride on the line...

00:15:02.980 --> 00:15:04.470
And the race has begun!

00:15:02.980 --> 00:15:06.980
Umamusume

00:15:02.980 --> 00:15:06.980
{\an2}Pretty Derby

00:15:09.830 --> 00:15:13.120
The horse girls are holding fairly 
tightly together as the race starts off.

00:15:13.120 --> 00:15:14.320
No one is lagging behind.

00:15:14.990 --> 00:15:19.330
Who will set the pace of this 
3,200 meter long distance run?

00:15:19.330 --> 00:15:20.490
Go!

00:15:20.490 --> 00:15:21.210
Which one?!

00:15:21.210 --> 00:15:21.820
Both!

00:15:21.820 --> 00:15:24.940
Will McQueen make the 
first move, or Tokai Teio?

00:15:26.640 --> 00:15:28.760
Oh, and Mejiro Palmer presses 
up from the outside!

00:15:28.760 --> 00:15:30.470
Wha?!

00:15:31.630 --> 00:15:33.970
Mejiro Palmer is now leading the race!

00:15:34.270 --> 00:15:36.110
Ultim-outrun!

00:15:36.110 --> 00:15:37.720
Here we go!

00:15:37.720 --> 00:15:40.630
McQueen is currently hovering 
around 6th and 7th place,

00:15:40.630 --> 00:15:43.370
with Tokai Teio moving into a 
similar position on the outside.

00:15:43.370 --> 00:15:45.230
McQueen is starting to push forward,

00:15:45.230 --> 00:15:48.570
with Tokai Teio holding 
steady slightly behind her.

00:15:48.780 --> 00:15:51.610
Everyone's attention is 
locked on these two,

00:15:51.610 --> 00:15:53.950
who are taking the center 
spotlight at this race!

00:15:53.950 --> 00:15:57.350
A 3,200 course is going to involve 
a lot of sudden shifts in pace.

00:15:57.350 --> 00:16:00.340
It demands a lot of stamina, 
focus, and racing know-how.

00:16:00.340 --> 00:16:01.330
What brought this on?

00:16:01.330 --> 00:16:04.250
There's a tendency to speed up
coming around the fourth corner

00:16:04.250 --> 00:16:06.210
in order to get the crowd on your side.

00:16:06.210 --> 00:16:07.910
But if you fall for that here,

00:16:07.910 --> 00:16:12.180
and blow the stamina needed for the 
final stretch, it won't do any good!

00:16:12.180 --> 00:16:14.680
I guess our cheering is just 
gonna get in the way, huh?

00:16:14.680 --> 00:16:18.840
The horse girls will now be 
passing the front-side stands.

00:16:18.840 --> 00:16:19.930
Here they come!

00:16:19.930 --> 00:16:21.010
McQueen-san!

00:16:21.010 --> 00:16:22.770
Teio-san!

00:16:22.770 --> 00:16:23.810
Go!

00:16:23.810 --> 00:16:26.250
Entering the home stretch of the first lap,

00:16:26.250 --> 00:16:29.000
and they're now passing in 
front of the majority of the seats.

00:16:29.000 --> 00:16:31.770
And the spectators are spurring them on!

00:16:30.280 --> 00:16:33.190
Come on! You can do it!

00:16:33.190 --> 00:16:34.860
Hang in there!

00:16:37.570 --> 00:16:39.950
It's so bumpy! It's hard to run on!

00:16:39.950 --> 00:16:42.620
Looks like the turf's 
gotten completely torn up.

00:16:42.620 --> 00:16:45.670
It takes real power to persevere. I wonder...

00:16:50.930 --> 00:16:53.610
I'll stick behind McQueen during 
the opening and mid game.

00:16:54.040 --> 00:16:57.090
And when we hit the third corner on 
the second lap, I'll make my move!

00:16:57.090 --> 00:16:59.540
The cheers have quieted down a bit,

00:16:59.540 --> 00:17:03.560
as Mejiro Palmer retains the lead,
 pulling the others along.

00:17:04.190 --> 00:17:08.310
I need to get a bigger lead!
 Come on! Dig deep!

00:17:09.090 --> 00:17:12.830
McQueen is currently in 4th place, 
with Tokai Teio in the middle of the pack.

00:17:12.830 --> 00:17:15.730
She's positioned herself so she 
can keep her eyes on Mejiro McQueen.

00:17:15.730 --> 00:17:18.070
I can see McQueen's moves from here!

00:17:20.580 --> 00:17:22.580
Which one is going to strike first?

00:17:22.580 --> 00:17:24.080
Who's it gonna be?!

00:17:24.080 --> 00:17:27.490
Rounding the second corner, 
they have now entered the backstretch.

00:17:27.490 --> 00:17:29.790
With the race reaching its final half,

00:17:29.790 --> 00:17:33.590
focus will be honing in on when 
Mejiro McQueen and Tokai Teio choose

00:17:33.590 --> 00:17:36.090
to enter their final spurt.

00:17:36.090 --> 00:17:38.720
The horse girls are now 
entering the third corner.

00:17:39.860 --> 00:17:42.030
Okay, here we go! Let's do it!

00:17:43.340 --> 00:17:46.680
Oh, and Tokai Teio is on 
the move! There she goes!

00:17:47.200 --> 00:17:48.440
Go!

00:17:48.440 --> 00:17:51.160
The incline of the third corner! This is it!

00:17:51.160 --> 00:17:55.030
But the spring winner's plaque is something 
that last year's winner, Mejiro McQueen,

00:17:55.030 --> 00:17:56.290
has no intention of ceding to another!

00:17:56.290 --> 00:18:00.300
Yet Tokai Teio is determined 
to walk away with it!

00:18:02.700 --> 00:18:05.070
They've now hit the 800 meter mark!

00:18:05.070 --> 00:18:07.730
We're entering unknown territory, 
an all-new distance for Tokai Teio!

00:18:07.730 --> 00:18:10.710
I trained so much! I can do this!

00:18:12.010 --> 00:18:14.710
Don't lose, Teio! Don't lose, McQueen!

00:18:14.710 --> 00:18:18.600
And McQueen is now in the lead!
 She is out in front!

00:18:18.600 --> 00:18:21.340
The horse girls are now 
entering the home stretch!

00:18:21.340 --> 00:18:25.000
Tokai Teio is hot on her tail!
 She's coming after her!

00:18:27.850 --> 00:18:30.350
Nothing's in my way! I can do this!

00:18:30.350 --> 00:18:32.360
Watch me, Prez!

00:18:35.460 --> 00:18:36.820
Teio's going for it!

00:18:36.820 --> 00:18:39.820
Whoa, and Tokai Teio presses even harder!

00:18:52.690 --> 00:18:54.650
Not bad, McQueen!

00:18:54.650 --> 00:18:57.630
But I'm gonna win this!

00:19:05.300 --> 00:19:09.450
I can't move up any further! Why? Why?!

00:19:09.450 --> 00:19:11.540
Is it me, or is she not looking 
as sharp as usual?

00:19:11.540 --> 00:19:12.910
And like she's having a hard time.

00:19:12.910 --> 00:19:14.940
This is where the distance 
is making a difference!

00:19:17.440 --> 00:19:19.550
But I trained so hard!

00:19:25.700 --> 00:19:29.330
I can't lose! I'm going to be undefeated!

00:19:29.680 --> 00:19:31.880
I promised the Prez!

00:19:33.790 --> 00:19:35.670
McQueen!

00:19:35.900 --> 00:19:38.430
McQueen is demonstrating miraculous speed!

00:19:38.430 --> 00:19:40.330
And what's happening to Tokai Teio?

00:19:40.330 --> 00:19:42.270
She's not gaining the way she normally does!

00:19:42.270 --> 00:19:44.100
Currently falling from third to fourth!

00:19:44.100 --> 00:19:48.510
Mejiro McQueen is still in the lead, 
with Kania Curation in second!

00:19:48.510 --> 00:19:52.410
Grace On Dance passes Tokai 
Teio and moves into third,

00:19:52.410 --> 00:19:55.520
but it doesn't look like anyone 
is catching up to Mejiro McQueen!

00:19:59.210 --> 00:20:00.780
She's amazing! More than amazing!

00:20:00.780 --> 00:20:04.010
The best stayer in modern racing,
 Mejiro McQueen!

00:20:04.010 --> 00:20:06.280
Her lead keeps expanding, 
and in first place—

00:20:06.280 --> 00:20:08.030
She crosses the goal!

00:20:08.030 --> 00:20:12.750
For the second time in a row, 
she has won the Spring Tennoushou!

00:20:16.540 --> 00:20:20.050
Mejiro McQueen has asserted her 
unassailable position of power!

00:20:20.620 --> 00:20:21.650
McQueen...

00:20:21.650 --> 00:20:23.160
Teio-san...

00:20:23.160 --> 00:20:24.550
Yay!

00:20:25.310 --> 00:20:26.720
Teio-san...

00:20:27.300 --> 00:20:30.590
I... I can't believe Tokai Teio lost.

00:20:31.580 --> 00:20:33.060
Not bad at all, McQueen!

00:20:33.060 --> 00:20:34.520
She did it!

00:20:47.270 --> 00:20:50.540
I've just never been in a long race before.

00:20:50.850 --> 00:20:53.410
We don't know if I'm any good at it or not.

00:20:53.650 --> 00:20:56.210
You can compensate for 
stamina with training...

00:20:56.210 --> 00:20:59.780
I wasn't able to become an undefeated 
Triple Crown horse girl.

00:20:59.780 --> 00:21:02.420
But I can keep being undefeated!

00:21:07.890 --> 00:21:10.890
K
y
o
t
o

00:21:07.890 --> 00:21:10.890
Results

00:21:32.320 --> 00:21:34.720
If you do lose, please try not to cry.

00:21:40.990 --> 00:21:42.300
McQueen...

00:21:47.260 --> 00:21:50.190
A consecutive Tennoushou... That's amazing.

00:21:52.810 --> 00:21:54.110
Teio...

00:21:54.810 --> 00:21:56.570
It was because of you...

00:21:56.930 --> 00:22:00.550
I'm only where I am today because of you.

00:22:00.550 --> 00:22:01.690
Teio—

00:22:04.600 --> 00:22:06.850
Congratulations, McQueen.

00:22:10.160 --> 00:22:12.140
Thank you, Teio.

00:22:19.960 --> 00:22:22.460
Congratulations, McQueen-san.

00:22:32.140 --> 00:22:34.660
I lost, huh?

